          {
            "title": "Critical MCP security flaw exposes 200,000 AI servers to RCE",
            "body": "OX Security researchers uncovered an architectural RCE vulnerability in Anthropic's Model Context Protocol, affecting 150M+ downloads and up to 200K server instances. Anthropic declined to patch, calling the behavior 'expected'. CVEs issued for LiteLLM, Windsurf, Cursor, Claude Code, and more, with several already patched.",
            "sources": [
              "https://venturebeat.com/security/mcp-stdio-flaw-200000-ai-agent-servers-exposed-ox-security-audit",
